article.headline: UNC Greensboro 80, Appalachian St. 76
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. (AP) -- Kyle Hines scored 33 points on 14-of-19 shooting to lead UNC Greensboro to an 80-76 win over Appalachian State on Thursday night. Neither team led by more than nine points during the game and both teams shot well from the floor. Appalachian State (13-5, 5-2) connected on 65 percent of its shots and UNC Greensboro (9-9, 6-2) shot 59 percent. UNC Greensboro also got 16 points from freshman Kendall Toney and 10 points from freshman Ben Stywall. With a balanced attack, Appalachian State closed out the first half on a 12-4 run to take a 42-38 lead at halftime. The teams traded leads in the second half before UNC Greensboro took a four-point lead with just under two minutes to play. The Spartans hit 7-of-10 free throws beginning with just over a minute remaining to seal the win. Demetrius Scott led Appalachian State with 16 points, while D.J. Thompson added 15 points and Donte Minter had 14.
